<CDLItem itemNbr="32-12-05" id="X-BOEING:FTID:81205.787.DDG.CU.CDL.3-32-12-05.1.3-32-12-05">
<Title>Main Landing Gear Trunnion Door</Title>
<DispatchCondition>
<DispatchConditionRemarks>
<Para>One may be missing provided gear remains extended for 10 minutes after takeoff and the takeoff performance adjustment is applied. Main landing gear trunnion door may not be missing in combination with main landing gear strut door or main landing gear lower strut door or main landing gear drag brace door.. </Para>
<Para>Limit speed to 270 KIAS / 0.73 Mach. </Para>
<Para>On the MISC SYSTEM CTRLS (MSC) maintenance page, set the Overspeed Warning switch to GEAR DOWN.</Para>
<Para>Procedure:
Do not retract landing gear for 10 minutes after takeoff. In the event of an engine failure after V1, retract the landing gear until a minimum of 1,500 feet above airport elevation and terrain clearance is assured. While maintaining terrain clearance, extend the gear for the balance of the 10 minutes.</Para>
<Para>For model 787-9 only: Apply the takeoff performance adjustment provided in the AFM Appendix 1, ’Performance Conditions and Procedures - Takeoff’ for main gear door opening not deactivated.</Para>
<Para>No additional weight reductions relative to AFM-DPI Gear Down Dispatch calculations are required for the 787-10.</Para>
<Para>Reduce performance limited weights by:</Para>
